  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8eb9d9fa0ccbe1b4cbcd2a1d889b806b, type: 3}
  m_Name: TenthDayConvo01
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  conversationName: TenthDayMainConversation
  lines:
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: Well, well, well... here we are. Your final shift.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Ten days. They\u2019ve been very productive, very profitable nights. I
      have to say, when you first walked in-- clueless, pen immediately signing a
      contract you didn\u2019t read-- I had my doubts. Briefly."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Well, not briefly. I had them this whole time. And it wasn\u2019t really
      \u2018doubt\u2019,  it was full confidence that you would inevitably fail to
      reach quota, and I would probably eat you. I had even picked out the spices,
      and--"
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Anyway, that doesn\u2019t matter now. You proved me wrong, and here you
      are-- alive and well! But don\u2019t get cocky, you still have one more quota
      to hit."
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: The final <b>quota</b> to hit is <b>[$quota]</b>. If you manage to reach
      it, you will have completed your contract. You will be free to... <i>depart</i>,
      muahaha.
  - speakerName: Randy
    line: "Hm? What was that suspiciously evil laugh? <i>Did I</i>  laugh? I didn\u2019t
      even notice. Anyway, work hard, and you have nothing to worry about, heh heh.
      Here, take a <b>room key</b>."
  repeatLine:
    speakerName: Randy
    line: Don't you have something else better to do?
